master
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ git start master
$ git verify


commit-one-file
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ git start next
$ git add A.txt
$ git commit -m "Some commit message"
$ git verify


commit-one-file-staged
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ git start next
$ git reset'
$ git add A.txt
$ git commit -m "Some commit message"
$ git verify


ignore-them
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ git start next
$ touch .gitignore
$ gedit .gitignore

/*------.gitignore------*/

*.exe
*.o
*.jar
libraries/

/*----------------------*/

$ git add .gitignore
$ git commit -m "Some commit message"
$ git verify


chase-branch
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ git start next
$ git status
$ git branch
$ git merge escaped
$ git verify



merge-conflict
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ git start next
$ git merge another-piece-of-work
$ git status
$ gedit equation.txt

/*-------equation.txt-----------*/

2 + 3 = 5
=======
2 + 3 = 5

/*------------------------------*/

$ git add equation.txt
$ git commit -m "Solved merge conflict"
$ git verify




save-your-work
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ git start next
$ git status
$ git stash
$ git stash list
$ git stash show
$ gedit bug.txt

/*---------bug.txt--------------------------*/

This file contains bug
It has to be somewhere.
I feel like I can smell it.
How this program could work with such bug?

/*-------------------------------------------*/

$ git add bug.txt
$ git commit -m "Fixed bug"
$ git stash pop
$ gedit bug.txt

/*---------bug.txt--------------------------*/

This file contains bug
It has to be somewhere.
I feel like I can smell it.
How this program could work with such bug?
This is the work I have done recently.
I would be very sad if I loose it.
Finally, finished it!

/*-------------------------------------------*/

$ git commit -am "Finally finished it"
$ git verify



change-branch-history
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ git start next
$ git rebase hot-bugfix
$ git verify


remove-ignored
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ git start next
$ git status
$ ls -lrt
$ cat .gitignore
$ git rm ignored.txt
$ git status
$ git commit -am "removed ignored.txt"
$ git status
$ git verify



case-sensitive-filename
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ git start next
$ git status
$ ls -lrt
$ git mv File.txt file.txt
$ git commit -am "Renamed filename"
$ git verify



fix-typo
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ git start next
$ git rebase -i
$ git status'
$ ls -lrt
$ gedit file.txt
$ git commit --amend '-S'
$ git add .
$ git commit --amend
$ git rebase --continue
$ git verify


forge-date
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ git start next
$ git status
$ git log
$ git commit --amend --date 19-11-1987
$ git verify



fix-old-typo
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ git start next
$ git rebase -i HEAD~2
$ gedit file.txt
fixed the typo
$ git add file.txt
$ git rebase --continue
$ gedit file.txt

/*-----------file.txt-------------------*/

Hello world
Hello world is an excellent program.

/*--------------------------------------*/

$ git add file.txt
$ git rebase --continue
$ git verify

















